  "title": "IT Security Architect (Cyber & Network)",
  "description": "<p>Looking for an experienced <strong>Security Architect </strong>with strong expertise in security, network design to lead the <strong>architecture and design </strong>of a security-centric program. The role is focused on <strong>strategy, design, and governance</strong>, while <strong>build and deployment activities will be executed by a customer-contracted third party.</strong><br /><br /><strong>Skills Required:</strong><br />Atleast 10+ years of experience in <strong>Cybersecurity & Network security</strong><br />Strong hands-on and architectural experience with at least 50% of the above-mentioned technologies.<br />Proven experience as a <strong>Security Architect.</strong><br />Experience working in environments where <strong>implementation is done by external vendors</strong><br />Strong understanding of:</p><ul><li>Privileged access controls</li><li>Authentication and authorization models</li><li>Identity governance</li><li>Security architecture frameworks</li></ul><p>Ability to translate business and security requirements into <strong>scalable technical designs</strong><br />Excellent documentation and stakeholder communication skills<br /><strong>Nice to Have</strong></p><ul><li>Experience with large enterprise or regulated environments</li><li>Knowledge of Zero Trust architecture</li><li>Relevant certifications (CyberArk, CISSP, CISM, etc.)</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Act as SME for the security technologies stated below.</li><li>Support the design and review of HLD and LLD submitted by customer third party, with a deep focus on security by design with reference to end customer cyber security management</li></ul><p><ul><li><strong>CyberArk</strong></li><li><strong>RSA</strong></li><li><strong>Privileged IAM (PIAM)</strong></li><li><strong>Citrix ADC (LLB) & Citrix ADM</strong></li><li><strong>Cisco ISE (TACCAS+)</strong></li><li><strong>Incognito DHCP</strong></li><li><strong>Akamai DNS Cache</strong></li><li><strong>ElasticSearch\\Logtash</strong></li></ul><ul><li>Customer security design policies</li><li>Regulatory and compliance requirements</li><li>Zero Trust / Least Privilege Principles</li></ul></p><p>Support stakeholder discussions, design workshops, and architecture reviews</p>",
